cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video surveillance and anomaly detection. The use of deep neural networks for feature learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the processing and analysis of multimedia data, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of one-class SVM models for anomaly detection suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
